[0.001, "o", "otherwise output encoding conversion cannot be performed"]
[0.000, "o", ".\u001b[K\r\u001b[31d;iconv.output_encoding =\r\u001b[33d[intl\r\u001b[34d;intl.default_locale =\u001b[K\u001b[35;3HThis directive allows you to produce PHP errors when some error\r\u001b[36d; happens within intl functions. The value is the level of the error produced.\r\u001b[37d; Default is 0, which does not produce any errors.\u001b[38;3HThis directive is deprecated.\u001b[K\r\u001b[39d;intl.error_level = E_WARNING\u001b[K\r\u001b[40d; If enabled this directive indicates that when an error occurs within an\u001b[41;3Hintl function a IntlException should be thrown.\r\u001b[42d; Default is Off, which means errors need to be handled manually.\r\u001b[43d;intl.use_exceptions = On\r\u001b[44d\u001b[K\u001b[45d[sqlite3]\u001b[K\u001b[41;23H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
